1) Expensive.  They cost around $25-$30 (canadian) for one pen.<br>
2) You can't just get variable line widths so yo uhave to switch back anf forth between pens of you have more than one.<br>
3) Hard to get accustomed too.  I took to them like a fish out of water, but some people have a hard time with them.<br>
<br>
There are good points about the pens though:<br>
1) Refillable...  In the long run you'll save money because you won't be buying new pens when they run out of ink.<br>
2) Excellent crisp lines.<br>
<br>
There are other peoblems with them too that you need to get accustomed to...  They have metal tips so you can't press hard cause you'll ruin the tip, as well you'll ruin the paper because it will cut through it like a dull xacto knife.<br>
